Class MechStage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.epoch.mechanisms.MechStage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ChemConstants, MechSynthConstants, FormatConstants, MechConstants, MechErrorConstants

    public class MechStage
extends Object
implements MechConstants
    Contains data and references to items inside a rectangle (box, stage).

      • calculateFlowProducts

        void calculateFlowProducts()
        Calculates and stores products of this stage's molecules and electron-flow arrows. Catches MechErrors and sets flowArrowsStatus, flowArrowsStatusStr, and flowArrowsProds accordingly.
        NOTE: We export the MechStage contents to an MDocument, then reimport it in MechSolver, so that we don't have to modify this stage's molecule or flow arrows, which could create inconsistencies for other calculations.

      • classifyMolecules

        void classifyMolecules(Molecule[] prevProducts,
                       int flags)
        Given the calculated e-flow products of previous stages, classify each molecule in this stage as response product/starter/intermediate.
        • A compound in a response is considered a RESPONSE PRODUCT if none of its atoms or bonds are sources or sinks of electron-flow arrows.
        • A compound in a response is considered a RESPONSE STARTING MATERIAL EITHER if it is in the first box, OR if it is not a RESPONSE PRODUCT AND the compound is NOT calculated to be produced from the electron-flow arrows of all previous stages of the mechanism.
        • A compound in a response is considered a RESPONSE INTERMEDIATE if it is neither a RESPONSE STARTING MATERIAL nor a RESPONSE PRODUCT.
        Parameters:
        prevProducts - products of previous stages in this mechanism
        flags - sets resonance permissiveness, double-bond isomer leniency

        boolean hasSourceOrSink(Molecule compound)
        Gets whether an electron-flow arrow of this stage touches a compound. Need to use original atom indices stored in each atom's properties, and not direct references to atoms, because original molecules may already have been replaced with clones.
        Parameters:
        compound - the compound
        Returns:
        true if an electron-flow arrow of this stage touches the compound

      • getMoleculeForAtom

        Molecule getMoleculeForAtom(MolAtom atom)
        Gets the molecule of this stage that contains an atom.
        Parameters:
        atom - an atom
        Returns:
        the molecule of this stage that contains the atom; null if the atom's parent is not in this stage

      • getMolecularity

        int getMolecularity()
        Counts the number of molecules in this stage that are touched by electron-flow arrows. We import an XML of the stage rather than using the stage's original molecules and MechFlows because we don't want the latter to become inconsistent.
        Returns:
        the number of molecules in this stage that are touched by electron-flow arrows

      • isEqualTo

        boolean isEqualTo(MechStage other)
        Gets whether a stage is equal to this one. Two stages are equal if they contain the same molecules and their calculated products are the same.
        Parameters:
        other - another stage
        Returns:
        true if the stage equals this one
